<item>
            <title>[SPARK-33611] Decode Query parameters of the redirect URL for reverse proxy</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-33611</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running Spark with reverse proxy enabled, the query parameter of the request URL can be encoded twice:  one from the browser and another one from the reverse proxy(e.g. Nginx).  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In Spark&apos;s stage page, the URL of &quot;/taskTable&quot; contains query parameter order&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;dir&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.  After encoding twice,  the query parameter becomes `order%255B0%255D%255Bdir%255D` and it will be decoded as `order%5B0%5D%5Bdir%5D` instead of  `order&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;0&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;dir&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;`.  As a result, there will be NullPointerException from &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/status/api/v1/StagesResource.scala#L176&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/status/api/v1/StagesResource.scala#L176&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Other than that, the other parameter may not work as expected after encoded twice.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should decode the query parameters and fix the problem&lt;/p&gt;</description>
